<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 3:17AM EDT  by NWS NorthernIndiana</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Wabash,
northwestern Grant, southeastern Cass and southern Miami Counties
through 400 AM EDT...
At 317 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Grissom Afb, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Grissom Afb around 320 AM EDT.
Bunker Hill around 325 AM EDT.
Peru around 335 AM EDT.
Other locations in the path of this storm include Wabash.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
